column1: # Table showing the comparison of consensus sequences generated from alignments of  the results of 100 simulations each of good quality, medium quality and poor quality Oxford Nanopore reads using BadRead [39] with the original input sequence.
# BadRead_Params: the set of BadRead parameters used (see Supplementary Methods)
# CIAlign_Stringency: None the alignment was not cleaned with CIAlign and Moderate if CIAlign cleaning was performed with moderate parameters
# Consensus_NW_Score, Consensus_Alignment_Length, Consensus_Percentage_Similarity and  Consensus_Percentage_Identity are as for Supplementary Table 2.
# Consensus_NW_Score: Needleman-Wunsch score for a consensus sequence generated from the alignment compared to the input sequence to BadRead
# Consensus_Alignment_Length, length of alignment of the consensus sequence with the input sequence
# Consensus_Percentage_Similarity: percentage similarity between the consensus sequence and the input sequence
# Consensus_Percentage_Identity: percentage identity between the consensus sequence and the input sequence
